As someone living in Europe, the fastest land animal would be the cheetah (Acinonyx jubatus). Cheetahs are native to some parts of Africa but have been introduced to other regions including parts of Europe. They can reach speeds up to 70 mph or about 112 km/h.

However, if we consider marine animals, then the sailfish from the Atlantic Ocean could be considered as one of the fastest aquatic creatures in Europe. Sailfish are known for their incredible speed and can swim at speeds up to around 68 mph (about 110 km/h).

Please note that these are estimates and actual speeds may vary based on various factors such as age, health, and environmental conditions.
